  "description": [
    "EDITORIAL PAGE Vol 11No 13 The Milwaukee Leader Entered as secondclass matter August 25 1920 at the postoffice at Milwaukee Wisconsin under the Act of March 3 1879 Published every evening except Sunday by the Milwaukee Social Democratic Publishing Company at Chestnut and Sixth Streets VICTOR L BERGER Editor On indefinite leave of absence and not responsible for contents of paper ASSOCIATE EDITORS E H THOMAS JOHN M WORK ASSISTANT MANAGER META BERGER 528 Chestnut St Milwaukee Wis SUBSCRIPTION RATESThe mail editions of The Milwaukee Leader will be sent to any subscriber in the United States for 150 for three months 300 for six months 600 for one year In foreign countries 5250 for four months 400 for six months SBOO for oqe year The Home Edition will be delivered in Milwaukee for 15c a week or 65 cents a month FOREIGN ADVERTISING REPRESENTATIVE IRALICK Si BATES Special Agency Tribune Bldg New York Chicago 1701 Heyworth Bldg Office Hours 8 A M to 6 P M 20 Tel Grand 5060 have NO DEATH AND NO TAXES They say that death and taxes are inevitable Some of our religious and psychological friends say they are going to prove that death is"
